cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. 

This paper focuses on interpretability in natural language processing, specifically in the task of Semantic Textual Similarity (STS). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely sub-categories. The task of STS involves measuring the degree of semantic equivalence between two sentences, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper's focus on user studies and human-computer interaction suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category.
